Goal:
Make sure role-based and ownership-based access is consistent across the core MVP modules.

Expected member logic:
1. A normal member should be able to:
   - view relevant organization data where appropriate;
   - update their own availability/readiness;
   - respond to callouts;
   - view notifications;
   - mark notifications as read if that exists;
   - view and update their own profile/member-related data where appropriate;
   - view, add, and edit their own personal equipment;
   - view their own certificates/qualifications if the module supports it;
   - view statistics if the current app design allows member statistics access;
   - add activities/trainings if the app design supports member-created activities or if there is an existing permission pattern for this.

2. A normal member must NOT be able to:
   - change their own organization role;
   - change other members’ roles;
   - change organization settings/details;
   - manage organization-owned equipment unless they are admin or another explicit permission exists;
   - edit another member’s personal equipment;
   - modify another organization’s data;
   - perform platform admin actions.

Expected admin logic:
